text:
Colonial Park: A view of the new playground and wading pool being constructed by the W. P. A. in the northern end of the Park. The photographers vantage point is on a line with W. 153rd Street and shows an elevated viaduct on what would be W. 155th Steeet.
March 16, 1936.
W. P. A. Photo
Federal Art Project
title: Manhattan: Colonial Park.

text:
Colonial Park: A view northward showing the new swimming pool under construction by the W.P.A. On the right appears buildings that line the east side of Bradhurst Ave., north from and including West 147th Street. This view is taken from the southern extremity of the Park, near 146th
Street.
March 16, 1937.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
title: Manhattan: Colonial Park.

text:
Colonial Park: The new swimming pool under construction by the W.P.A. This view is southward from a point near West 147th Street and shows the southern extremity of the Park. Across the background is West 145th Street (southernmost edge) with buildings upon the south side of same, between Bradhurst (left) and Edgecombe (right) Aves. These are numbered 320 to 338 respectively.

March 16, 1937.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
title: Manhattan: Colonial Park.
